{"key":"post-9969470","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9969470</id>\n<content>Don't try to add as much water as the verm holds.&amp;nbsp; Mix one part water with two parts verm and stir well until it's all absorbed, and then add one part brown rice flour.&amp;nbsp; In other words, use the same amount of water as rice flour, but twice as much verm.&amp;nbsp; Load your jars up to the glass threads on the jar, and top the last 1 1/2 cm with dry verm, which serves as your filter.&amp;nbsp; Watch all four parts of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;this video&lt;/a&gt; before you start.&amp;nbsp; It will save you from making the normal new grower mistakes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Note the recipe above is for use with fine or medium grade verm.&amp;nbsp; If you're using coarse verm, cut back about 20% on the amount of water, since course verm doesn't absorb as much.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9969318</prev>\n<first>9968847</first>\n<last>9969470</last>\n<when>1237046724</when>\n<utime>03/14/09 07:05 PM</utime>\n</post>"}